Revision history for markdown

0.14 2026-05-07
    - changed `.docx` input with no target to recover sibling markdown by default
    - added explicit `.docx` to `.md` and `.md` to `.docx` routes
    - implemented the new office-document markdown routes by chaining through the existing PDF backends

0.13 2026-05-07
    - added `.docx` to `.pdf` routing to `dashboard markdown.convert`
    - added explicit `.pdf` to `.docx` routing when the target path ends in `.docx`
    - added LibreOffice dependency files for Linux and macOS office-document routes
    - added Windows and macOS Office backend selection for DOCX/PDF conversion

0.12 2026-05-06
    - added an explicit MIT license to the `markdown` skill
    - documented the MIT license in the README

0.11 2026-04-30
    - added ISO paper sizes `A0` through `A10`, `B0` through `B10`, and `C0` through `C7`
    - added `DL` and `ANSI-A` through `ANSI-E` paper sizes for markdown-to-pdf output
    - extended `-A` shorthand support to `0` through `10`

0.10 2026-04-30
    - fixed real PDF table-cell wrapping so long values stay inside their own cells
    - made PDF table rows grow vertically to fit wrapped filename, path, and action text
    - fixed PDF text-width measurement to honor actual `PDF::API2` font metrics instead of only the test stub metrics

0.09 2026-04-30
    - fixed the real default PDF renderer so selected paper size and orientation reach `PDF::API2`
    - proved generated `-A 3 --landscape` PDFs use an A3 landscape media box on Linux and macOS

0.08 2026-04-30
    - added `-A {1,2,3,4}` as shorthand for `--paper A1|A2|A3|A4`
    - reject duplicate paper-size selection when `--paper` and `-A` are both given
    - added installed runtime proofs for shorthand paper selection on Linux and macOS

0.07 2026-04-30
    - added `--paper` with `A1`, `A2`, `A3`, and `A4` support for markdown-to-pdf
    - added `--landscape` and `--portrait` with portrait as the default pdf orientation
    - made markdown-generated html tables emit `border="1"`
    - added runtime proofs for A3 landscape pdf output on Linux and macOS

0.06 2026-04-30
    - changed markdown-to-pdf table handling from flattened text rows to drawn table cells
    - stripped inline markdown markers from pdf table cell content
    - added PDF table rendering proofs with realistic multi-column data on Linux and macOS

0.05 2026-04-30
    - added a skill-local `Markdown::Enhancer` layer on top of the CPAN stack
    - fixed markdown tables so html output renders real `<table>` markup
    - fixed inline code so html and pdf output no longer show raw backticks
    - normalized table rendering for pdf output so raw pipe syntax is not left visible

0.04 2026-04-30
    - replaced the remaining external document converters with a Perl-only module stack
    - removed `aptfile` and `brewfile` in favor of `cpanfile`
    - switched markdown-to-pdf rendering to `PDF::API2`

0.03 2026-04-30
    - made positional file arguments the primary CLI flow for `markdown.convert`
    - added visible stderr progress logging for long-running conversion steps

0.02 2026-04-30
    - replaced the macOS pdf package contract with `weasyprint`
    - added runtime fallback from `wkhtmltopdf` to `weasyprint` for markdown to pdf conversion

0.01 2026-04-30
    - created the initial `markdown` skill with CLI conversion support for markdown, html, and pdf
    - added Docker-verified tests for route selection, output naming, and fake-tool conversion flows
